1
00:00:00,465 --> 00:00:03,820
If you have time,
let's hang out sometime.

2
00:00:03,820 --> 00:00:06,500
Not just a meal after work,

3
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:09,780
but a movie or something.

4
00:00:09,780 --> 00:00:12,850
I want to learn more about you, Onuma-san.

5
00:00:12,850 --> 00:00:17,150
You know,
Kusaka-kun is surprisingly strong mentally.

6
00:00:17,150 --> 00:00:18,675
What do you mean?

7
00:00:18,675 --> 00:00:21,225
I was seen...

8
00:00:21,225 --> 00:00:24,180
going into your room.

9
00:00:24,180 --> 00:00:25,645
- Miporin!
- You're too loud!

10
00:00:25,645 --> 00:00:27,925
Just shut up and get in!

11
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,550
Huh?

12
00:00:36,970 --> 00:00:39,920
Why didn't you tell me?

13
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:44,650
What would you do if I did?

14
00:00:45,530 --> 00:00:48,010
Would you have...

15
00:00:48,856 --> 00:00:50,926
not let me in?

16
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:57,400
You're the worst.

17
00:01:04,765 --> 00:01:08,140
He's the worst...

18
00:01:08,140 --> 00:01:10,400
The worst!

19
00:01:30,980 --> 00:01:33,080
He's the worst.

20
00:01:35,730 --> 00:01:39,580
♫ It's hard to resist the thing
that I've missed for so long ♫

21
00:01:39,580 --> 00:01:41,350
♫ So long ♫

22
00:01:41,350 --> 00:01:45,160
♫ Can't remember what it's like,
Just remember I need it ♫

23
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:47,610
♫ I need it ♫

24
00:01:47,610 --> 00:01:51,880
♫ You're not what I thought you were ♫

25
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,770
♫ You were ♫

26
00:01:53,770 --> 00:01:57,250
♫ To think I can't find a cure ♫

27
00:01:57,250 --> 00:01:59,790
♫ Find a cure ♫

28
00:01:59,790 --> 00:02:05,920
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

29
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:16,320
[If Only You Weren't the One]

30
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:22,930
[Episode 6]

31
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:24,480
I'm sorry, Onuma-san.

32
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:27,270
I have to pick up my kid,
so I'm about to head out.

33
00:02:27,270 --> 00:02:30,000
- Will you be okay?
- I'll clock out later.

34
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,986
Sorry about this, but I'll be going ahead.

35
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:34,768
- Good work today.
- Thanks for your hard work.

36
00:02:34,768 --> 00:02:36,320
Thanks for your hard work.

37
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:39,760
- I'm off! Thanks for your hard work.
- Bye.

38
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:41,800
Thanks for your hard work.

39
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,490
The meeting ran long, huh?

40
00:02:43,490 --> 00:02:44,965
- It was long.
- Yeah.

41
00:02:44,965 --> 00:02:48,510
- I'll compile the minutes.
- Thank you.

42
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:50,830
- When's our reservation?
- It's 6:30 p.m.

43
00:02:50,830 --> 00:02:52,920
We're a bit early, but let's go.

44
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,909
It's near the company,
and they've got pretty lights.

45
00:02:55,909 --> 00:02:59,705
- It's super pretty!
- Oh, sounds nice.

46
00:02:59,705 --> 00:03:02,590
- Shall we go then, Yuri-chan?
- Okay!

47
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:14,815
Thank you very much.

48
00:03:14,815 --> 00:03:17,760
And once again, I'm Yukina, from Hokkaido.

49
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:20,620
I turned 20 this month.

50
00:03:22,975 --> 00:03:25,940
No matter how painful or lonely it was,

51
00:03:25,940 --> 00:03:30,351
I didn't want to lose to myself,
so I poured my soul into writing this.

52
00:03:30,351 --> 00:03:32,281
Please enjoy.

53
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:39,410
♪ When spring comes ♪

54
00:03:39,410 --> 00:03:43,770
♪ After I open my eyes ♪

55
00:03:43,770 --> 00:03:47,840
♪ I want to tell you ♪

56
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:53,490
♪ You, the most important person in my world ♪

57
00:04:03,825 --> 00:04:06,750
I've been in Tokyo for 12 years.

58
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:10,550
With both work and love left half-hearted,

59
00:04:11,670 --> 00:04:15,700
I'm about to welcome yet another new year.

60
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:26,900
I moved to Tokyo with Satoshi-kun,
whom I dated in high school.

61
00:04:28,735 --> 00:04:33,580
I figured that's just how things were.

62
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:35,750
Are you and Satoshi-kun getting along?
[Mom]

63
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:37,675
Our parents get along well, too.

64
00:04:37,675 --> 00:04:40,305
He's such a nice boy.

65
00:04:40,305 --> 00:04:43,090
I feel at ease
knowing Satoshi-kun is by your side.

66
00:04:43,090 --> 00:04:46,295
"I feel at ease
knowing Satoshi-kun is by your side,"

67
00:04:46,295 --> 00:04:50,805
had become my mother's catchphrase.

68
00:04:52,195 --> 00:04:54,030
Uh, I'm Eisei Ureshino.

69
00:04:54,030 --> 00:04:57,940
I guess whoever I fall for becomes my type.

70
00:04:57,940 --> 00:04:59,440
Huh?

71
00:05:00,310 --> 00:05:02,430
Hey.

72
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:04,640
Wait a second.

73
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:07,090
Hm?

74
00:05:18,135 --> 00:05:24,550
Back then, if I hadn't met Eisei,
I'd probably be...

75
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:44,880
[Satoshikawaguchi]
[At Hachinohesaka Shrine during our honeymoon.]

76
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:24,660
Miporin.

77
00:06:25,660 --> 00:06:28,720
Why didn't you pick up the phone yesterday?

78
00:06:35,850 --> 00:06:37,898
Are you ignoring me?

79
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:41,600
What? Don't talk to me.

80
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,736
Huh?

81
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:46,870
Are you upset
I went on a date with Yuri-chan?

82
00:06:46,870 --> 00:06:48,150
What?

83
00:06:48,150 --> 00:06:51,470
If you're lonely, you could just say so.

84
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:54,250
That's not why I'm mad.

85
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:56,930
And it's none of my business.

86
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:59,840
Oh?

87
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:06,180
Then, why so cold?

88
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:14,240
I can't be like you.

89
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:17,240
Huh?

90
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:23,340
Have you ever thought
about Kusaka-kun's feelings?

91
00:07:25,435 --> 00:07:27,030
Good morning.

92
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:29,855
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

93
00:07:59,450 --> 00:08:01,870
You're my partner in crime.

94
00:08:08,115 --> 00:08:12,240
And, so, this was the biggest scoop
I picked up.

95
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:15,480
I managed to find out
about Ureshino-san's love life!

96
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:17,090
- What?
- Really?

97
00:08:17,090 --> 00:08:19,490
Mihono-san, do you think he has anyone?

98
00:08:19,490 --> 00:08:22,390
I'm not sure. Doesn't matter to me.

99
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:25,190
You should show more interest!

100
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:27,300
The correct answer is...

101
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,890
he doesn't!

102
00:08:28,890 --> 00:08:31,550
Oh, really? So, there really isn't anyone.

103
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:34,570
Actually, I was a bit suspicious

104
00:08:34,570 --> 00:08:38,515
Ureshino-san might have
something with Mihono-san.

105
00:08:38,515 --> 00:08:40,105
Right?

106
00:08:41,205 --> 00:08:43,710
- Yeah.
- You two seem really close.

107
00:08:43,710 --> 00:08:46,800
And calling you "Miporin"
obviously means you're special!

108
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,410
That? He's just teasing me.

109
00:08:49,410 --> 00:08:53,100
- And since the company trip, everyone's been gossiping.
- No way.

110
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:58,955
So, when he said out loud,
"I don't have anyone I like,"

111
00:08:58,955 --> 00:09:01,915
I felt relieved.

112
00:09:03,377 --> 00:09:05,060
- That's great.
- Yeah.

113
00:09:05,060 --> 00:09:07,110
- Will you get dinner again?
- I hope so!

114
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:08,855
Hope he invites you again next time.

115
00:09:08,855 --> 00:09:11,445
You think he will?

116
00:09:26,645 --> 00:09:28,340
Onuma-san.

117
00:09:28,340 --> 00:09:29,820
Yes?

118
00:09:29,820 --> 00:09:33,810
I'd like to settle this account
before next week's presentation.

119
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:35,935
Could you look at it?

120
00:09:35,935 --> 00:09:37,865
Understood.

121
00:09:43,460 --> 00:09:45,580
Check your messages.

122
00:10:06,370 --> 00:10:08,160
Onuma-san.

123
00:10:09,595 --> 00:10:12,260
Please don't be so startled.

124
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:15,595
Sorry, sorry. What is it?

125
00:10:15,595 --> 00:10:18,660
Can I walk you to the station?

126
00:10:20,090 --> 00:10:22,540
Yeah, sure.

127
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:33,950
By the way, about that date...

128
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:40,640
Oh, sorry, things have been a bit hectic.

129
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,750
- I haven't really...
- It's fine.

130
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,405
Oh.

131
00:10:48,405 --> 00:10:51,130
Do you like movies?

132
00:10:51,130 --> 00:10:54,854
There are a lot of good ones
starting this week.

133
00:10:54,854 --> 00:10:58,158
Oh? Sounds good.

134
00:10:58,158 --> 00:11:02,598
I haven't been to a cinema in a while,
so I'd be happy to go.

135
00:11:02,598 --> 00:11:04,690
Great.

136
00:11:04,690 --> 00:11:07,570
Then, it's settled.

137
00:11:08,796 --> 00:11:10,666
Yeah.

138
00:11:10,666 --> 00:11:14,680
You must be a movie expert,
if you know the new releases.

139
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:18,230
I'm not really an expert, but I do like them.

140
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:20,075
I can watch any genre,

141
00:11:20,075 --> 00:11:23,325
so let's pick something
you're interested in.

142
00:11:24,155 --> 00:11:25,620
Thanks.

143
00:11:25,620 --> 00:11:28,410
I'll take a look too then.

144
00:11:28,410 --> 00:11:30,620
What are you usually watching?

145
00:11:30,620 --> 00:11:32,130
What's wrong?

146
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,460
Can I make a quick call?

147
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:35,960
Sure.

148
00:12:09,005 --> 00:12:10,570
Kusaka-kun.

149
00:12:10,570 --> 00:12:13,360
Onuma-san, good morning.

150
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:15,030
Morning.

151
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:16,975
This is my first time here.

152
00:12:16,975 --> 00:12:20,275
It's a really nice theater.

153
00:12:20,275 --> 00:12:23,230
I really like independent theaters.

154
00:12:23,230 --> 00:12:25,970
They're like secret bases.

155
00:12:26,940 --> 00:12:29,700
Oh, let's go to our seats.

156
00:13:07,625 --> 00:13:11,115
- That was fun.
- Yeah.

157
00:13:11,115 --> 00:13:13,270
- Wow.
- I didn't know they had this.

158
00:13:13,270 --> 00:13:15,696
There are so many.

159
00:13:15,696 --> 00:13:19,685
Onuma-san, which ones are you interested in?

160
00:13:19,685 --> 00:13:22,830
Hmm... This one?

161
00:13:22,830 --> 00:13:26,705
Oh, I'm interested in this one, too.

162
00:13:26,705 --> 00:13:30,095
- It says February.
- You're right.

163
00:13:30,095 --> 00:13:34,360
Oh, in that case,
let's go see this together.

164
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:35,950
Sounds good.

165
00:13:35,950 --> 00:13:38,190
It's a promise.

166
00:13:38,190 --> 00:13:39,610
Yeah.

167
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:44,090
Oh, this scene was so great, wasn't it?

168
00:13:44,090 --> 00:13:46,510
Thank you.

169
00:13:46,510 --> 00:13:48,140
Enjoy.

170
00:13:48,862 --> 00:13:51,770
Whoa! This part was super moving.

171
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:53,695
Yeah.

172
00:13:53,695 --> 00:13:55,800
Onuma-san, which part did you like?

173
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:58,360
Let's see... Oh, this scene.

174
00:13:58,360 --> 00:14:02,190
Man, that part was really great, too.

175
00:14:02,190 --> 00:14:06,880
- Yeah.
- It was so good. Wow...

176
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:11,910
I wonder what do I want with Kusaka-kun?

177
00:14:14,175 --> 00:14:16,670
Being together is fun.

178
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:19,315
Will we just chill like friends?

179
00:14:19,315 --> 00:14:21,115
Oh.

180
00:14:21,115 --> 00:14:24,690
Onuma-san, do you have any requests for dinner?

181
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:28,665
- A guy I'll just keep around?
- Some good places around here.

182
00:14:28,665 --> 00:14:31,575
That's not what I want.

183
00:14:33,550 --> 00:14:35,990
Sorry, Kusaka-kun.

184
00:14:37,330 --> 00:14:38,730
Huh?

185
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:44,710
Back at the inn, you saw, didn't you?

186
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:54,055
I knew it. You're dating, aren't you?

187
00:14:56,190 --> 00:14:58,470
We're not dating.

188
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:03,140
That's not what it is.

189
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:11,240
I know it's wrong.

190
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:15,380
I'm really sorry.

191
00:15:16,710 --> 00:15:19,150
Please don't apologize.

192
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:26,190
That... makes it harder for me.

193
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:37,390
I noticed from the start
that there was something there.

194
00:15:37,390 --> 00:15:40,770
But it can't be helped.

195
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:47,440
They say the one
who falls in love loses, don't they?

196
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:59,600
That's why I hate...

197
00:16:03,790 --> 00:16:08,750
seeing how you don't value yourself.

198
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:15,830
I don't want to just be a convenient guy
to have around.

199
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:27,360
I'm sorry.

200
00:16:28,530 --> 00:16:30,430
Oh...

201
00:16:30,430 --> 00:16:32,420
I'm sorry.

202
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,520
Sorry.

203
00:16:38,570 --> 00:16:41,030
Thank you for today.

204
00:17:14,815 --> 00:17:18,620
[Eisei Ureshino]

205
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:20,540
Seriously?

206
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:23,400
I didn't call him, though.
Nor have I seen him.

207
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:25,230
No contact, right?

208
00:17:25,230 --> 00:17:26,840
Basically.

209
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:28,048
- Here.
- Thanks.

210
00:17:28,048 --> 00:17:32,003
- For how long?
- Hmm. About a week.

211
00:17:32,780 --> 00:17:36,060
So, you haven't forgotten him, huh?

212
00:17:37,558 --> 00:17:42,250
Actually, hearing your story,
I thought, can't you choose Kusaka?

213
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:44,000
Huh?

214
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,165
He's kind, cute,
and you share interests, right?

215
00:17:47,165 --> 00:17:48,995
Yeah.

216
00:17:48,995 --> 00:17:52,838
I personally think he's pretty great.

217
00:17:52,838 --> 00:17:56,609
Honestly, I've never once heard you say

218
00:17:56,609 --> 00:17:58,570
what you like about Eisei Ureshino.

219
00:17:58,570 --> 00:17:59,940
Hold on.

220
00:17:59,940 --> 00:18:01,430
Is that true?

221
00:18:01,430 --> 00:18:03,415
It is. You only complain.

222
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:06,135
No way!

223
00:18:06,940 --> 00:18:12,650
But, well, I could list things
I hate about him all day though.

224
00:18:25,330 --> 00:18:28,190
Isn't that just liking him too much?

225
00:18:30,010 --> 00:18:32,340
That's rough.

226
00:18:43,365 --> 00:18:44,760
Merry Christmas!

227
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:47,737
On special days like Christmas...

228
00:18:47,737 --> 00:18:49,960
- It's amazing!
- Nice, right?

229
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:53,350
- I got chocolate cake.
- Nice. It's huge.

230
00:18:53,350 --> 00:18:56,190
- I'll go get some plates.
- Okay, thanks.

231
00:18:56,190 --> 00:18:58,595
we both had other people,

232
00:18:58,595 --> 00:19:01,865
so we never spent time together.

233
00:19:06,246 --> 00:19:10,990
[Eisei Ureshino sent a sticker.]
[I want to see you, Miporin.]

234
00:19:10,990 --> 00:19:16,460
[Merry Christmas!]
[I want to see you, Miporin.]

235
00:19:20,285 --> 00:19:22,610
If there's any left, we can have it tomorrow.

236
00:19:22,610 --> 00:19:24,910
Yeah. That's true.

237
00:19:27,868 --> 00:19:30,721
- Here.
- Thanks.

238
00:19:31,505 --> 00:19:36,850
Because I can't have it,
my desire grows even stronger.

239
00:19:36,850 --> 00:19:39,610
How about a Christmas cake?

240
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:43,105
One, please.

241
00:19:43,105 --> 00:19:46,945
- Thank you for waiting.
- Thank you.

242
00:19:46,945 --> 00:19:48,890
Welcome.

243
00:19:48,890 --> 00:19:51,970
Okay, one cake? Got it.

244
00:20:11,155 --> 00:20:12,530
Kusaka-kun...

245
00:20:12,530 --> 00:20:16,150
Kusaka-kun, I'm sorry about before.

246
00:20:16,150 --> 00:20:21,295
I really want to talk properly,
so how about a meal sometime?

247
00:20:37,875 --> 00:20:41,150
I should be the one apologizing
for being one-sided.

248
00:20:41,150 --> 00:20:43,845
I'd be happy to. Let's meet.

249
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:53,030
I hope he likes it.

250
00:20:54,954 --> 00:20:57,991
[Worldrise Travel]

251
00:20:59,590 --> 00:21:02,150
Good morning.

252
00:21:03,710 --> 00:21:05,620
Yuri-chan?

253
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:09,530
Looks like she got rejected.

254
00:21:09,530 --> 00:21:12,680
- Huh?
- By Ureshino-san.

255
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:20,230
Everyone's talking about it.

256
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:27,160
Telling her the truth is true kindness.

257
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,490
Got it.

258
00:21:38,490 --> 00:21:42,210
Good work.

259
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:43,650
You turned her down?

260
00:21:43,650 --> 00:21:46,865
Huh?

261
00:21:46,865 --> 00:21:48,730
What are you talking about?

262
00:21:48,730 --> 00:21:51,670
But she's so cute.

263
00:21:51,670 --> 00:21:54,670
Onuma-san, can I ask you to handle this?

264
00:21:54,670 --> 00:21:56,610
Thank you.

265
00:21:58,010 --> 00:22:01,350
Huh, you did reject her?

266
00:22:04,930 --> 00:22:09,630
♫ I kept looking at you ♫

267
00:22:09,630 --> 00:22:15,315
♫ Hold me close, stay by my side ♫

268
00:22:15,315 --> 00:22:17,020
Hey, did you hear about us?

269
00:22:17,020 --> 00:22:18,330
Don't talk to me.

270
00:22:18,330 --> 00:22:19,745
It's fine.

271
00:22:19,745 --> 00:22:22,190
No, it's not.

272
00:22:22,190 --> 00:22:25,780
Jeez, you're so serious, Miporin.

273
00:22:25,780 --> 00:22:28,930
I don't want to complicate things.

274
00:22:29,990 --> 00:22:32,890
Who cares about the rumors?

275
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:36,350
It's not okay.

276
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,780
It's a bother.

277
00:22:48,010 --> 00:22:49,876
Fine.

278
00:22:59,350 --> 00:23:04,090
How about we go for it?

279
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:08,270
Huh?

280
00:23:12,290 --> 00:23:17,460
What if we actually started dating?

281
00:23:30,585 --> 00:23:33,210
I like you. Please go out with me.
[Preview]

282
00:23:33,210 --> 00:23:35,115
I made you uncomfortable.

283
00:23:35,115 --> 00:23:37,875
I'm the one...

284
00:23:37,875 --> 00:23:39,780
who made you uncomfortable.

285
00:23:39,780 --> 00:23:42,760
Can you stand not meeting Ureshino-san
until next year?

286
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:45,515
I kept trying to block it out...

287
00:23:45,515 --> 00:23:46,870
Oh, it's Christmas today.

288
00:23:46,870 --> 00:23:48,780
Our first Christmas together.

289
00:23:48,780 --> 00:23:50,565
Are you going home?

290
00:23:50,565 --> 00:23:52,385
I like you.

291
00:23:53,980 --> 00:23:57,140
Let's skip out on the after-party.

292
00:23:57,140 --> 00:24:00,030
[This drama is fiction.]
